">           Before we delve into whether or not committing genocide on harmful intelligences is ever morally justified, we must first decide what is is that makes an intelligence “harmful”. The first part of this definition is easy; harmful simply refers to something that causes harm. However, the second part proves to be more challenging: what is harm? Moral philosopher Bernard Gert asserts that there are “five harms that all rational persons want to avoid” (1). These five harms are as follows:

                               1. Don’t kill (Don’t cause permanent loss of consciousness.)
                               2. Don’t cause pain. (This includes mental pain as well as physical pain.)
                               3. Don’t disable. (Don’t cause loss of ability.)
                               4. Don’t deprive of freedom (or opportunity).
                               5. Don’t deprive of pleasure. (Gert 10)

           Therefore, a “harmful intelligence” is an intelligent being or species that knowingly causes one of the five harms or does not knowingly cause harm but cannot be changed so that it no longer does. Through this, it is immediately clear why The Terminator should be considered a harmful intelligence. It’s sole reason for existence was to go back in time, find Sarah Connor, and murder her (Cameron, <i>The Terminator</i>). It is more difficult to judge whether or not the noocytes are harmful. However, the noocytes ultimately deprive humanity of freedom. Specifically, they deprive them of the freedom to choose whether they would like to remain as an individual human or join the noosphere. For the most part, the noocytes transform people without their permission, such as between Edward and Gail, when they merged together (Bear, 114). Still, it may be argued that at one point noocytes gave Suzy the choice to “continue like [she was], or to join us” (Bear, 219). Ultimately, though, the noocytes changed Suzy, as well as the rest of humanity (Bear, 275-276). Therefore, both the noocytes and the Terminator are to be considered “harmful”
</p>
